The comparison to abuse is apt, it’s a pattern of behaviour from people who are bad at arguing or who are upset by the idea that they should ever have to. Who are upset by privileged people committing the crime of remaining confident in their opinions until convinced differently.

I will absolutely say that the whole thing reminds me of my past abusive relationship. Literally not even reading what you say. Assuming like 5 absurd things from every one of your statements that do get read. Asserting that you just aren’t listening if you continue to disagree.

Then contra & tons of other people keeps behaving like he just, didn’t listen to her? Or anybody else? & that the Kat convo had anything to do with the misogyny itself? I wish people besides myself with criticisms of him were capable of knowing his position & arguing for theirs.

He argued for what felt like an eternity with Kat and for most of it she literally said she wasn’t reading his stuff even after saying she was interested in hearing him out. She inserted like a dozen assumptions that he never implied or said he believed. It was horrendous.
